SQL Tutorials
Overview of DML:
1. DML stands for "Data Manipulation Language".
2. DML is used to insert, update and delete records.
3. ALL DML commands are temporary commands.
What is DML?
By using DML commands we can insert a record to an existing table and also, we can update, delete the exciting records from the table.
Syntax for inserting record:
They are 3 ways to insert records into a table
1. In first one we are going to insert only one record by using column_names and respective values
Syntax: Insert into table_name (column_name1, column_name2, column_name3, ............................)
Values (value1, value2, value3, .........................);
Examples:
2. In second one we are going to insert only one record by using only respective values of columns
Syntax: Insert into table_name Values (value1, value2, value3, .........................);
Examples:
3. In third one we are going to insert multiple records at a time
Syntax: Insert all into table_name Values (value1, value2, value3, .........................)
into table_name Values (value1, value2, value3, .........................)

Syntax for updating record:
Syntax: update table_name set colunm_name = “new_value”
Where condition;
NOTE: where condition is not mandatory. If we fail to give where condition all the mentioned column values will change to new_value
Examples:
Syntax for deleting a record:
Syntax: Delete table_name
Where condition;
